In this proclamation, President Donald Trump declares May 2017 as Jewish American Heritage Month. He highlights the strong American Jewish heritage rooted in the faith and traditions of the Jewish people. Trump acknowledges the contributions of American Jews in various fields such as culture, education, and philanthropy. He also recognizes their role in promoting human freedom, equality, and dignity. The President expresses gratitude for the deep spiritual connection between the Jewish people and the United States, and encourages all Americans to celebrate Jewish American heritage and observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.